 Responsibilities 
The  Digital Sales Representative  is an experienced solution seller with a proven track record of selling cloud-based business process automation solutions across customersâ€™ lines of business with experience developing demand, owning and running ERP/CRM sales pursuits and acquiring customer adds. 
To excel in the Business Applications Digital Sales Representative role, you must have the following traits and abilities: 
Business Process Transformation Knowledge-  Has understanding of business process transformation challenges and opportunities and can envision solutions mapped with business value to address customer persona business needs and pains. 
Business Decision Maker Conversationalist, Digital First Seller - Identifies the right BDMs and builds relationships virtually using social selling best practices leveraging other organizations in Microsoft and their relationships. Expertise in customer-centric solutions with connected use cases to achieve trusted advisor role with BDMs & customer personas. 
Orchestrator-  Multi-thread Project Manager, influences for impact, leads, manages & drives shared vision and execution across virtual teams and partners .
 Business Outcome Seller-  Ability to map solution capabilities addressing customer persona needs and pains with business value leveraging pre-defined business value maps.
